President Obama has announced his intent to nominate Jeffrey A. Rosen for the position of Governor on the Board of Governors of the United States Postal Service. Rosen is currently a Senior Partner at Kirkland & Ellis LLP and has extensive experience in federal service, including roles as General Counsel and Senior Policy Advisor for the White House Office of Management and Budget, and General Counsel at the Department of Transportation. He is also involved in various legal and business organizations, including serving as Chair of the American Bar Association's Section of Administrative Law & Regulatory Practice. Rosen holds a B.A. from Northwestern University and a J.D. from Harvard Law School.